This paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on policy gradient methods, which are commonly used in control problems. The use of emphatic weightings is a novel contribution to the field, which suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm called Actor Critic with Emphatic weightings (ACE), which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with optimization and convergence, which are topics that fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
